headline: J.P. Morgan Chase (JPM) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: Jeremy Barnum: Thank you, and good morning, everyone.  Expenses of $24 billion were up 5% year on year, predominantly driven by higher volume and revenue-related expenses and compensation growth, including from office hiring, partially offset by the release of an FDIC special assessment accrual.  This quarter's higher standardized RWA is driven by increases in lending across both wholesale and retail including the Apple Card purchase commitment, which contributed about $23 billion of standardized RWA partially offset by lower market risk RWA.

content.title: J.P. Morgan Chase (JPM) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
content.summary: Jeremy Barnum: Thank you, and good morning, everyone.  Expenses of $24 billion were up 5% year on year, predominantly driven by higher volume and revenue-related expenses and compensation growth, including from office hiring, partially offset by the release of an FDIC special assessment accrual.  This quarter's higher standardized RWA is driven by increases in lending across both wholesale and retail including the Apple Card purchase commitment, which contributed about $23 billion of standardized RWA partially offset by lower market risk RWA.
